def remove_numbers(text):
  return ' '.join([i for i in str(text).split() if not i.isdigit()])

twitter['tweet'] = twitter['tweet'].apply(lambda x: remove_numbers(x))

- remove numbers¶

In [15]:
def remove_numbers(text):
  return ' '.join([i for i in str(text).split() if not i.isdigit()])

twitter['tweet'] = twitter['tweet'].apply(lambda x: remove_numbers(x))

- removing links¶

In [16]:
def remove_weblinks(text):
  return re.sub(r"http\S+", "", text)

twitter['tweet'] = twitter['tweet'].apply(lambda x: remove_weblinks(x))

- removing mentions¶

In [17]:
def remove_twitter(text):
  return re.sub('@[\w]+','',text)

twitter['tweet'] = twitter['tweet'].apply(lambda x: remove_twitter(x))

- removing punctuation¶

In [18]:
def remove_punctuation(text):
  return text.translate(str.maketrans('','', string.punctuation))

twitter['tweet'] = twitter['tweet'].apply(lambda x: remove_punctuation(x))

- removing stop words¶

In [22]:
eng_stopwords = set(stopwords.words('english'))

def remove_stopwords(text):
  return " ".join([word for word in str(text).split() if word not in eng_stopwords])

twitter['tweet'] = twitter['tweet'].apply(lambda x: remove_stopwords(x))

- lemmatization¶

In [29]:
lemmatizer = WordNetLemmatizer()

wordnet_map = {"n": wordnet.NOUN, "v": wordnet.VERB, "j": wordnet.ADJ, "r": wordnet.ADV}

def lemmatize_words(text):
    pos_tagged_text = nltk.pos_tag(text.split())
    return " ".join([lemmatizer.lemmatize(word, wordnet_map.get(pos[0], wordnet.VERB)) for word, pos in pos_tagged_text])

twitter['tweet'] = twitter['tweet'].apply(lambda text: lemmatize_words(text))

- tokenization¶

In [30]:
tokenizer = TweetTokenizer(preserve_case=False, strip_handles=True,
                               reduce_len=True)

def tokenize_tweet(tweet):
    tweet_tokens = tokenizer.tokenize(tweet)
    return tweet_tokens
